headline: Delta Air Lines Balances Major Fleet Orders With Winter Disruption Risks
summary: Delta Air Lines (NYSE:DAL) announces orders for 31 new Airbus widebody aircraft as part of a fleet refresh. The company also agrees to acquire up to 60 Boeing 787-10 aircraft, expanding long haul capabilities. At the same time, severe winter weather in the Northeast triggers major operational disruptions and flight suspensions at key airports.
